gomodel:SYNGO_5076  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: \"When hippocampal cultures at DIV 6 were stained for both Mena (gene ENAH) and the presynaptic inhibitory synaptic vesicle protein VIAAT, Mena containing 'hot spots' were clearly observed along dendrites and in neuronal somata (Figs. 6A, A1). Furthermore, although there was a considerable amount of diffusely localized protein, approximately 68% (data not shown) of these Mena puncta colocalized with VIAAT (Figs. 6A, A1). ... Costaining with fluorescently labeled phalloidin showed that Mena puncta were aligned with F-actin in dendrites (Fig. 6A2).\". Experimental description: M&M: \"Hippocampal neurons were isolated from rat hippocampi of embryonic day 18 rat embryos and maintained as described previously (Fuhrmann et al., 2002).\"\n\nantibody:\nhuman ena/VASP (M4, rabbit, T. Renne, University of Wuerzburg, Germany: see Halbrugge et al., 1990)\n\nselected rat protein accession was based on BLAST of mouse swissprot entry Q03173-1 (Neural variant Mena+++, 140 kDa isoform)" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2023-02-23" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_5076" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

